comment: Towns (MIN) sets the screen on Clarkson (LAL) and gives him room to avoid the contact.
Randle (LAL) sets the screen on Rubio (MIN) and gives him room to avoid the contact.
Towns (MIN) makes body to body contact with Clarkson (LAL) that affects his jump shot attempt.
Nwaba (LAL) and Wiggins (MIN) briefly engage and separate off ball.
Randle (LAL) is in a legal guarding position and blocks the driving shot attempt by Towns (MIN). The contact to the hand following the block is considered incidental.
Nance Jr. (LAL) sets the screen on Wiggins (MIN) and gives him room to avoid the contact.
Randle (LAL) sets the screen on Dunn (MIN) and gives him room to avoid the contact.
Towns (MIN) maintains legal guarding position and makes incidental contact with Randle (LAL) that does not affect his drive to the basket and shot attempt.
[Observable in enhanced video] Wiggins (MIN) moves his pivot foot.
Clarkson (LAL) legally contests Rubio's (MIN) jump shot attempt. Any "high-five" contact after the release is considered incidental.
Wiggins (MIN) makes incidental contact with Randle (LAL) during rebounding.
Clarkson (LAL) makes contact to Wiggins' (MIN) arm that affects his shot attempt.
Nwaba (LAL) falls to the floor as a result of the contact with his teammate Randle (LAL).
Dunn (MIN) maintains legal guarding position defending Russell (LAL) on the perimeter.
Russell (LAL) maintains legal guarding position and makes incidental contact with Rubio (MIN) that does not affect his SQBR.
